00:11:48.530 --> 00:11:50.140
Okay?

253
00:11:50.170 --> 00:11:52.740
"Does my sister have two sons?"

254
00:11:52.770 --> 00:11:54.020
"No, she doesn't."

255
00:11:54.050 --> 00:11:55.460
She has one son, right?

256
00:11:55.490 --> 00:12:01.128
So "she does not" becomes "she doesn't."

257
00:12:01.328 --> 00:12:02.820
She doesn't.

258
00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:04.460
It's a contraction.
She doesn't.

259
00:12:04.490 --> 00:12:05.340
She does not.

260
00:12:05.370 --> 00:12:09.300
Okay, we say "Does my sister?"
and "she does".

261
00:12:09.330 --> 00:12:11.340
We use that verb, "do".

262
00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:12.980
It's called an auxiliary verb.

263
00:12:13.010 --> 00:12:15.660
But I should not explain
to you the grammar rule.

264
00:12:15.680 --> 00:12:19.768
You just consume, consume
and you will learn this the natural way.

265
00:12:19.968 --> 00:12:20.140
Right?

266
00:12:20.170 --> 00:12:22.540
He is my nephew.
It's my sister's son.

267
00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:24.460
You see here we have
that same thing again.

268
00:12:24.490 --> 00:12:27.020
My nephew.
"Yes, he is."

269
00:12:27.050 --> 00:12:29.760
Okay, here we go.

270
00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:34.740
Let's see if there are
any unknown words here.

271
00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:38.100
"My aunt and my uncle,
they live outside the city."

272
00:12:38.130 --> 00:12:41.380
"Do my aunt and uncle
live in the city center?"

273
00:12:41.410 --> 00:12:43.020
"In the center of the city?"

274
00:12:43.050 --> 00:12:44.460
"No, they don't."

275
00:12:44.490 --> 00:12:46.820
Because they live outside the city.

276
00:12:46.850 --> 00:12:48.600
Right?

277
00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:50.060
Okay.

278
00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:52.100
Yeah, I think that's about it.

279
00:12:52.130 --> 00:12:54.060
"My family likes to play soccer."

280
00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:58.220
"Does my family like to play baseball?"

281
00:12:58.250 --> 00:13:01.460
Baseball is another American
common sport, right?

282
00:13:01.490 --> 00:13:03.140
"No, they don't."

283
00:13:06.370 --> 00:13:08.980
Okay.
All right.

284
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:10.020
Yep, that's about it.

285
00:13:10.050 --> 00:13:11.260
Remember, "don't ask why."

286
00:13:11.290 --> 00:13:13.640
I know it is very, very tempting to say,

287
00:13:13.670 --> 00:13:17.620
"but Kale, why are they using this verb,
and how does that work?"

288
00:13:17.650 --> 00:13:21.460
"And what is the word order
and what is the conjugation?"

289
00:13:21.480 --> 00:13:22.980
"I don't understand this and that."

290
00:13:23.010 --> 00:13:24.180
Don't ask why.

291
00:13:24.210 --> 00:13:26.220
Don't ask why.
Trust me.

292
00:13:26.250 --> 00:13:27.420
Trust in your coach.

293
00:13:27.450 --> 00:13:29.300
Because if you ask why, all the time.

294
00:13:29.330 --> 00:13:33.100
And if you get all the explanations
that you want, you're going to get so

295
00:13:33.130 --> 00:13:37.900
frustrated over time because there's so
many rules, there's so many definitions,

296
00:13:37.930 --> 00:13:43.900
there's so many grammar concepts that if
you try to understand why on everything,

297
00:13:43.920 --> 00:13:46.420
you're just going to get confused
and you're going to lose fluency,

298
00:13:46.450 --> 00:13:49.900
lose confidence, and you're
not gonna improve as fast.

299
00:13:49.930 --> 00:13:52.540
Okay, so what do you want to do now?

300
00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:54.180
Listen to the normal version 2 to 3 times,

301
00:13:54.210 --> 00:13:56.974
then listen to the interactive
version 10 times

302
00:13:57.174 --> 00:13:58.620
or as many times as you need

303
00:13:58.650 --> 00:14:02.140
in order to be able to respond
to the questions without looking.

304
00:14:02.160 --> 00:14:03.900
Remember, you can download the audios

305
00:14:03.920 --> 00:14:06.500
and the transcripts if you want
to practice outside the course,

306
00:14:06.530 --> 00:14:10.700
if you're on an airplane,
if you are at a place where you don't have

307
00:14:10.720 --> 00:14:13.800
internet, you can click here,
download transcript and audio file and it

308
00:14:13.830 --> 00:14:16.420
will download to your
phone or to your computer.

309
00:14:16.450 --> 00:14:18.940
And remember, you can go
to the next section only...

310
00:14:18.970 --> 00:14:23.540
You may continue to the next section only
when you're able to answer all

311
00:14:23.570 --> 00:14:26.700
the questions in the interactive
version, correctly!

312
00:14:26.720 --> 00:14:28.180
And how do you
answer the questions?

313
00:14:28.210 --> 00:14:30.700
You say "yes" or "no".
Boom.

314
00:14:30.730 --> 00:14:33.620
Correctly, out loud.
Not like this.

315
00:14:33.650 --> 00:14:36.340
Yes, no, yes, no, yes.

316
00:14:36.370 --> 00:14:40.540
Like confidently, on time, without
looking at the transcript, okay?

317
00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:45.700
And remember, input creates output.
Okay?

318
00:14:45.730 --> 00:14:51.340
So I know it's frustrating to not be able
to speak intuitively automatically

319
00:14:51.370 --> 00:14:54.420
in a language when we're just
starting and that's natural.

320
00:14:54.450 --> 00:14:55.460
We need more input.

321
00:14:55.480 --> 00:14:56.760
We need more input like this.

322
00:14:56.790 --> 00:15:00.900
We need to consume these stories over and
over and over and over and over again.

323
00:15:00.930 --> 00:15:02.860
Listening turns into speaking.

324
00:15:02.890 --> 00:15:04.660
Reading turns into writing.
Okay?

325
00:15:04.690 --> 00:15:09.020
So it's only natural that your speaking
is worse than your listening, okay?

326
00:15:09.050 --> 00:15:12.150
It's not about talking
in the mirror...

327
00:15:12.351 --> 00:15:13.820
Don't waste your time

328
00:15:13.850 --> 00:15:17.220
talking English into the mirror,
practicing speaking like that.

329
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:20.780
Focus on listening, consuming,
and you will internalize vocabulary

330
00:15:20.810 --> 00:15:24.940
and grammar structures in your brain,
which is a requisite to be able to speak,

331
00:15:24.970 --> 00:15:27.420
to produce the language
automatically, fluently.

332
00:15:27.450 --> 00:15:29.380
Okay?
That is how it works.

333
00:15:29.400 --> 00:15:32.900
And if you wanna practice speaking or if
you want to practice conversations

334
00:15:32.930 --> 00:15:35.340
with other students to gain more
confidence,

335
00:15:35.370 --> 00:15:40.140
to get rid of fear and anxieties
and things like that in a non-judgmental

336
00:15:40.160 --> 00:15:42.500
environment, you can join
the RAIO Conversation Club.

337
00:15:42.520 --> 00:15:45.580
You can get a private coach as well if
you want to accelerate your learning.

338
00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:47.980
Maybe if you have a very specific need,

339
00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:51.940
maybe if you're a football player and need
to learn like vocabulary and talk about

340
00:15:51.970 --> 00:15:54.540
football as fast as possible,
get a private coach.

341
00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:56.260
We have that as well.
We're here to help you.

342
00:15:56.290 --> 00:15:59.020
I will talk about this more in section 18,

343
00:15:59.050 --> 00:16:03.900
but you can check out
that right now if you want to.

344
00:16:03.930 --> 00:16:06.300
More information is below
chapter number six.

345
00:16:06.330 --> 00:16:09.200
Okay, now let's get
started with the exercise.

346
00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:09.460
Okay?

347
00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:13.460
But before you get started
consuming the stories here below,

348
00:16:13.490 --> 00:16:14.580
repeat after me!

349
00:16:14.610 --> 00:16:20.600
"I'll become fluent in English.
I'll never give up on my goal."

350
00:16:24.160 --> 00:16:25.820
Great.
Boom.

351
00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:27.060
Awesome.
Okay, great.

352
00:16:27.080 --> 00:16:29.180
Now keep going.

353
00:16:29.200 --> 00:16:32.060
Listen to the normal version then
listen to the interactive version.

354
00:16:32.080 --> 00:16:34.820
And then I'll see you
in section number three.

355
00:16:34.850 --> 00:16:36.500
Remember, take a break.

356
00:16:36.530 --> 00:16:41.540
I mean, if you want to, you can
keep going and keep up that speed, right?

357
00:16:41.570 --> 00:16:44.660
But remember, consistency over
intensity, very important.

358
00:16:44.690 --> 00:16:45.980
Alright?
Good luck.

359
00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:46.720
See you in the next one.

